Class DatabaseCrawler<T>

java.lang.Object
  org.madeirahs.shared.database.DatabaseCrawler<T>

Direct Known Subclasses:
Database.StringCrawler, Database.TimeValueCrawler
abstract class DatabaseCrawler<T>
extends Object
implements Comparator<T>

Represents an implementation of Comparator used to crawl the Collections Database. Subclasses should override the compare method specified by Comparator and implement it according to the following specifications:

  • T a and T b should both be compared to the initialized query variable in this superclass.
  • The return value of compare should be -1 if a is less similar to query than b, 0 if equally similar and 1 if more similar.
  • If either a or b are null, an IllegalArgumentException should be thrown, and comparison should NOT take place.
  • The process by which a and b are compared to query should be similar to the relevance determination in isRelevant. The difference is that isRelevant should return false for completely irrelevant values, while compare should just determine relative similarity.


Note: Due to the third party comparison technique specified by this class, it is not required nor expected that all subclasses meet all Comparator criteria. Instead, it is left up to the implementor to determine how this criteria should apply to calculating relative similarities between each variable and the query.

Author:
Brian Groenke
